COLUMELLA.

Of Gallinae some are court-yard birds, others again are wild, others are African. The court-yard bird is that which commonly is seen at nearly every country- house. The wild sort, which is not unlike that of the countryâ€”house, is trapped by bird-catchers. lt is abundant in the island lying in the Ligurian sea, which sailors, lengthening the bird's name out, have called continuously Gallinaria.
